Outside of the share button, have you already inserted the Facebook JS SDK?

Currently, the only thing that `enabled: true/false` controls is whether or not the JS SDK is dynamically inserted into the DOM.

When `true` it runs the following:

``` coffeescript
# CoffeeScript
inject_facebook_sdk: ->
    if !window.FB && @config.networks.facebook.app_id && !@el.body.querySelector('#fb-root')
      script      = document.createElement("script")
      script.text = "window.fbAsyncInit=function(){FB.init({appId:'#{@config.networks.facebook.app_id}',status:true,xfbml:true})};(function(e,t,n){var r,i=e.getElementsByTagName(t)[0];if(e.getElementById(n)){return}r=e.createElement(t);r.id=n;r.src='#{@config.protocol}connect.facebook.net/en_US/all.js';i.parentNode.insertBefore(r,i)})(document,'script','facebook-jssdk')"

      @el.body.innerHTML += "<div id='fb-root'></div>"
      @el.body.appendChild(script)
```

``` javascript
// JavaScript
  Share.prototype.inject_facebook_sdk = function() {
    var script;
    if (!window.FB && this.config.networks.facebook.app_id && !this.el.body.querySelector('#fb-root')) {
      script = document.createElement("script");
      script.text = "window.fbAsyncInit=function(){FB.init({appId:'" + this.config.networks.facebook.app_id + "',status:true,xfbml:true})};(function(e,t,n){var r,i=e.getElementsByTagName(t)[0];if(e.getElementById(n)){return}r=e.createElement(t);r.id=n;r.src='" + this.config.protocol + "connect.facebook.net/en_US/all.js';i.parentNode.insertBefore(r,i)})(document,'script','facebook-jssdk')";
      this.el.body.innerHTML += "<div id='fb-root'></div>";
      return this.el.body.appendChild(script);
    }
  };
```

@jenius You're correct. 

If the user uses the FB SDK outside of the share button they are required to include the FB JS SDK and `#fb-root`. Currently, we're checking if `#fb-root` exists and not if it has content. The problem is that this leaves us open to the possibility that the FB JS SDK wasn't ever initialized. This could be due to developer error, etc. Regardless, it means that the FB portion of the share button won't work.

By checking that `#fb-root` has content, we ensure that (along with `window.FB`) it was successfully initialized.

